@baseUrl = http://localhost:5101
@adminKey = devXXXdev
@mcpKey = devMcpKey

### Health — Liveness
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Health — Readiness
GET {{baseUrl}}/ready

### Health — Readiness (alias)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health/ready

###

# ── Admin — Books ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All admin requests require X-Admin-Api-Key header.
# Lifecycle: register (multipart upload) → ingest-blocks (no-LLM end-to-end) → optional delete.

### Admin Books — Register a PDF (stays Pending; call /ingest-blocks to process)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/register
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="PlayerHandbook2014.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./PlayerHandbook2014.pdf
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="version"

Edition2014
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="displayName"

PlayerHandbook 2014
------Boundary
# bookType: Core | Supplement | Adventure | Setting | Unknown (optional, defaults to Unknown)
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="bookType"

Core
------Boundary
# fivetoolsSourceKey (optional): e.g. PHB, MM, XGE — links this book to a 5etools source for SRD/group metadata
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="fivetoolsSourceKey"

PHB
------Boundary--

### Admin Books — List all books
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/books
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

# Block extraction is performed by the MinerU service (layout-aware, multi-column-correct).
### Admin Books — Ingest blocks (layout-aware PDF extraction via MinerU + bookmark metadata, embed direct to dnd_blocks)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/ingest-blocks
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Ingest entities (reads books/canonical/<book>.json and persists structured entities)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/ingest-entities
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Project structured facts (canonical JSON tables/choice-sets → Postgres)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/project-structured
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Extract entities (LLM-driven; writes books/canonical/<book>.json). Initial run only.
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/extract-entities
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Re-extract entities (force overwrite of existing canonical JSON)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/extract-entities?force=true
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Re-extract only failed entities (requires existing canonical JSON)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/extract-entities?errorsOnly=true
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Entity recall check (official books only; ?type=Monster|Spell|MagicItem|God; report-only diff of canonical entities vs the 5etools roster — present/grounded/backfilled/missing/extra (split into extraOtherSource/extraUnknown), no write)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/entity-recall?type=Monster
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Backfill missing entities from 5etools (official books only; ?type=Monster|Spell|MagicItem|God; fills parser gaps, appends dataSource:"5etools-backfill" entities). For MagicItem the roster also includes templated +N variants expanded from magicvariants.json (e.g. "+1 Longsword"), and Descriptions are richly flattened from 5etools entries (nested lists/tables/sub-entries, inline tags reduced to display text).
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/backfill-entities?type=MagicItem
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Fill missing structured fields on existing canonical entities from 5etools (official books only; fill-missing-only merge via the allowlist, never overwrites an extraction/human field, skips dataSource:"manual" entities; 409 if no canonical file exists yet)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/fill-fields
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Flag unknown extra entities for review (official books only; ?type=Monster|Spell|MagicItem|God; sets needsReview:true on canonical entities whose name matches no 5etools entity under any source — extraUnknown; never deletes, never touches extraOtherSource)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/flag-unknown-entities?type=Monster
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Re-ground NeedsReview entities (Tier 0/1 only; fast, no LLM judge)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/reground-entities
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Re-ground with the Tier 2 qwen3 judge (slow; promotes grounded, flags fabrications)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/reground-entities?judge=true
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Entity recall with an unsupported ?type (400 Problem response listing supported types)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1/entity-recall?type=Plane
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — needsReview triage — List flagged entities (all books, all reasons, first 50)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/needs-review
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — needsReview triage — List flagged entities filtered by book and reason
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/needs-review?book=phb14&reason=low-confidence&offset=0&limit=50
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — needsReview triage — Get a single entity by id (returns full EntityEnvelope)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/phb14.spell.fireball
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — needsReview triage — Resolve: accept (clear the NeedsReview flag only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/phb14.spell.fireball/resolve
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "action": "accept" }

### Admin — needsReview triage — Resolve: edit (apply name correction + clear flag)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/phb14.monster.b-ullywug/resolve
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "action": "edit", "name": "Bullywug" }

### Admin — needsReview triage — Bulk-accept all low-confidence entities for a book
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/needs-review/accept
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "book": "phb14", "reason": "low-confidence" }

### Admin — needsReview triage — Bulk-accept ALL flagged entities (no filter)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/entities/needs-review/accept
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Admin — Validate the entire canonical corpus
# Response shape:
# { "filesScanned": N, "totalEntities": N, "failures": [], "warnings": [],
#   "needsReview": [{ "file": "tce.json", "count": 156 }] }
# needsReview: entities flagged for human review (name quality). Not errors — returns 200.
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/canonical/validate
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Normalize entity names in canonical JSONs (title-case ALL-CAPS, flag OCR artifacts)
# Response: { filesScanned, totalEntities, dryRun, changes: [{ file, titleCased, flagged, unchanged }] }
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/canonical/normalize
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Normalize (dry-run — shows counts without writing files)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/canonical/normalize?dryRun=true
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Fix canonical entity types for a book using 5etools reference
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/canonical/fix-types?book=tce
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Rebuild global BM25 corpus statistics from the current ingested corpus (COR-15)
# Recomputes DocumentCount / AvgDocLength / DocFrequencies across all books. Returns 200 on success.
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/bm25/rebuild-stats
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Corpus-wide duplicate entity report (dedup)
# Response: DuplicateReport { groupCount, loserCount, groups: [{ winnerId, loserIds, ... }] }
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/entities/duplicates
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Compact duplicate entities (dry-run — reports without deleting)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/entities/compact
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Compact duplicate entities (apply — deletes the loser entities)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/entities/compact?apply=true
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — One-time backfill: stamp source_key onto existing dnd_blocks (stable source_key migration)
# Idempotent — safe to re-run. Response: { perBook: { "PHB": n, "MM": n, ... }, total }
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/backfill-source-keys
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin Books — Delete a book record and all associated data
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/books/1
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — Import all 5etools JSON files directly into dnd_entities
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/5etools/import
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Admin — List all 5etools sources (full list)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/5etools/sources
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Admin — List 5etools sources filtered by group (e.g. core, setting, supplement, adventure)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/5etools/sources?group=core
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

# ── Qdrant — Direct collection management ─────────────────────────────────────
# Call these directly against Qdrant (port 6333), not the app.
@qdrantUrl = http://localhost:6333
@collectionName = dnd_blocks

### Qdrant — Delete entire collection (wipes all vectors; app recreates it on restart)
DELETE {{qdrantUrl}}/collections/{{collectionName}}

### Qdrant — Collection info (point count, status)
GET {{qdrantUrl}}/collections/{{collectionName}}

###

# ── Retrieval ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# version: Edition2014 | Edition2024
# category: Spell | Monster | Class | Race | Background | Item | Combat | Adventuring | Condition | God | Plane | Treasure | Encounter | Trap | Trait | Lore | Rule

### Retrieval — Public semantic search
GET {{baseUrl}}/retrieval/search?q=fireball&version=Edition2024&category=Spell&topK=5

### Retrieval — Filter by bookType (Core | Supplement | Adventure | Setting | Unknown)
GET {{baseUrl}}/retrieval/search?q=fireball&bookType=Core&topK=5

### Retrieval — Diagnostic search (admin, includes scores and Qdrant point IDs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/search?q=fireball&version=Edition2024&category=Spell&topK=5
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Retrieval — Get entity by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/retrieval/entities/test-book.class.fighter

### Retrieval — Vector search over entities
GET {{baseUrl}}/retrieval/entities/search?q=swashbuckler&type=Subclass

### Retrieval — Search monsters by CR range and keyword (keywords come from 5etools traitTags e.g. Amphibious, Pack Tactics)
GET {{baseUrl}}/retrieval/entities/search?q=swamp&type=Monster&crNumeric_lte=2&keyword=Amphibious&topK=5

### Retrieval — Admin diagnostic entity search (full fields + pointId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/entities/search?q=fireball&type=Spell&spellLevel=3
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

### Retrieval — Entity search filtered to SRD 5.2.1 only
GET {{baseUrl}}/retrieval/entities/search?q=fireball&srd52=true&topK=5
Accept: application/json

###

### Retrieval — Admin entity search with SRD 5.2.1 filter (diagnostic)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/retrieval/entities/search?q=fireball&srd52=true&topK=5
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

# ── MCP Server ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The /mcp endpoint uses the Model Context Protocol (Streamable HTTP transport).
# It speaks JSON-RPC 2.0, not REST — use an MCP client, not curl.
# Configure AI clients with:
#   URL:    http://localhost:5101/mcp
#   Header: X-Mcp-Api-Key: devMcpKey
# Available tools: search_lore, search_entities, get_entity
#
# Verify the endpoint is alive (returns 405 Method Not Allowed for GET — that is correct):
GET {{baseUrl}}/mcp
X-Mcp-Api-Key: {{mcpKey}}

###

# ── Observability ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# /metrics is guarded by the admin API key (SEC-09, AdminApiKeyMiddleware) and
# only mapped when OpenTelemetry:Enabled is true.

### Metrics — Prometheus scraping endpoint (requires X-Admin-Api-Key)
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics
X-Admin-Api-Key: {{adminKey}}

###

# ── Web UI (Blazor) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The same host serves the Blazor Server UI: /login, /register, /campaigns,
# /heroes, /chat (interactive, cookie-authenticated — open in a browser).

### Web UI — Logout (clears the auth cookie, redirects to /login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/logout
